cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 

1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper focuses on the use of massive MIMO technology to improve data rates and link reliability in wireless networking. This falls under the domain of information theory, making cs.IT the most likely sub-category.

2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the design and implementation of a wireless networking system, which is a key area of research in networking and internet architecture.

3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper presents a system model and link-level simulation to validate the design and performance of the algorithms used in the system. This falls under the domain of systems and control.

4. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper describes the hardware design of a 128-antenna massive MIMO prototyping system, which falls under the domain of hardware architecture.

5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper mentions the transmission of real-time video and downlink data, which falls under the domain of multimedia.
